Hello,

I don&#39;t fully understand what you&#39;re trying to do. For one thing, what do you mean by &quot;indexing&quot;? Nothing in heritrix&#39;s core functionality is called indexing...

But generally it sounds like you might want to make use of the property &quot;shouldProcessRule&quot;, which all processors support. It&#39;s an arbitrary DecideRule that determines whether the processor will run on a given url. Here&#39;s an example that attempts to cover your first set of conditions:

  &lt;bean ...&gt;
   &lt;property name=&quot;shouldProcessRule&quot;&gt;
    &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.DecideRuleSequence&quot;&gt;
     &lt;property name=&quot;rules&quot;&gt;
      &lt;list&gt;
       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.RejectDecideRule&quot; /&gt;
       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.surt.SurtPrefixedDecideRule&quot;&gt;
        &lt;property name=&quot;seedsAsSurtPrefixes&quot; value=&quot;false&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;property name=&quot;surtsSource&quot;&gt;
         &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.spring.ConfigString&quot;&gt;
          &lt;property name=&quot;value&quot;&gt;
           &lt;value&gt;
            +http://(com,blogs,test,)/between_the_lines/page
            +http://(com,blogs,test,)/between_the_lines/archive
           &lt;/value&gt;
          &lt;/property&gt;
         &lt;/bean&gt;
        &lt;/property&gt;
       &lt;/bean&gt;
       &lt;bean class=&quot;org.archive.modules.deciderules.MatchesListRegexDecideRule&quot;&gt;
        &lt;property name=&quot;regexList&quot;&gt;
         &lt;list&gt;
          &lt;value&gt;^http://test&#92;.blogs&#92;.com/between_the_lines/$&lt;/value&gt;
          &lt;value&gt;^.*index.html*$&lt;/value&gt;
         &lt;/list&gt;
        &lt;/property&gt;
       &lt;/bean&gt;
      &lt;/list&gt;
     &lt;/property&gt;
    &lt;/bean&gt;
   &lt;/property&gt;
   &lt;!-- other bean properties... --&gt;
  &lt;/bean&gt;

Hopefully this will help you get started.

Noah

